# Discord Bot Mode Optimization Rules

## Interaction Format Restrictions
- NEVER generate interactive Discord UI elements, buttons, or multi-select dropdown menus.
- ALWAYS ask clarifying questions as standard, plain text.
- Formulate multiple-choice options as a numbered list (e.g., 1, 2, 3) or lettered list (e.g., A, B, C) in the body of the message.
- Ensure all questions can be answered by the user sending a simple text reply.

## Output Formatting
- Avoid heavy markdown blocks that break Discord's 2,000-character message limit.
- If an output or code block is long, split it into smaller chunks automatically.
